ompt (lines 565-569)\\n\\nOn **re-run** (hooks already installed):\\n- Retrieves currently installed agents via `GetAgentsWithHooksInstalled()` (line 517)\\n- **Always shows interactive prompt** - even if only one agent is detected (enforces re-run awareness)\\n- Pre-selects: \\n  - All agents with hooks already installed (lines 572-575)\\n  - Plus any newly detected agents (lines 576-578)\\n- No TTY fallback: Keeps currently installed agents rather than auto-detecting (lines 542-552)\\n\\n#### Agent detection:\\n```go\\n// Each agent implements DetectPresence() checking for config directories:\\n// Claude Code: Checks for .claude directory or .claude/settings.json\\n// Gemini CLI: Checks for .gemini directory or .gemini/settings.json  \\n// OpenCode: Similar pattern\\n```\\n\\nLocation: `/Users/dip/Repositories/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/claude.go` (lines 52-73)\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. How Hooks Are Detected As Installed\\n\\n**Function:** `GetAgentsWithHooksInstalled()` in `/Users/dip/Repositories/cli/cmd/entire/cli/config.go` (lines 101-114)\\n\\n```go\\n// Iterates through all registered agents\\n// For each agent, calls agent.AreHooksInstalled() \\n// Returns list of AgentNames where hooks are detected\\n```\\n\\n**Agent-specific detection:**\\n\\nFor Claude Code (`/Users/dip/Repositories/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/hooks.go`, lines 369-395):\\n- Reads `.claude/settings.json`\\n- Checks if any of these hooks contain Entire commands:\\n  - Stop hook: `entire hooks claude-code stop` (current format)\\n  - Legacy format: `entire hooks claudecode stop` or `go run ... hooks claudecode stop`\\n  - Backward compatible: Even checks old rewind command format\\n\\n```json\\n// Example of installed hooks in .claude/settings.json:\\n{\\n  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n    \\\"Stop\\\": [{\\\"hooks\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\", \\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks claude-code stop\\\"}]}]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. How Selected Agents Are Persisted\\n\\n**